{
    "name":  "Moroccan Chickpea Stew",
    "instructions":  "1. Heat the olive oil in a large pot over medium heat. Add the onion and garlic; cook until onion is translucent, about 5 to 7 minutes.  \n\n2. Stir in the ground cumin, ground coriander, garam masala, cayenne pepper, curry powder, and salt; cook until fragrant, about 1 minute.  \n\n3. Add the potatoes, diced tomatoes, tomato sauce, and raisins; add enough water to cover mixture. Bring to a simmer; cook until potatoes are soft, about 10 to 15 minutes.  \n\n4. Add the kale and chickpeas; simmer until kale wilts, about 3 minutes.  \n\n5. Sprinkle cilantro over stew; immediately remove pot from the heat.",
    "simpleInstructions":  "1. Sauté onion and garlic.  \n\n2. Add spices and cook briefly.  \n\n3. Simmer potatoes, tomatoes, and raisins.  \n\n4. Add kale and chickpeas, cook until kale wilts.  \n\n5. Garnish with cilantro and remove from heat.",
